\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.js\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n&lt;add path=\"*.gif\" verb=\"GET,HEAD\" type=\"EPiServer.Web.StaticFileHandler, EPiServer\" /&gt;\r\n\r\nThe EPiServer installation files seem to include a version of the web.config for IIS 6 and one for IIS 7. There are located in <strong>C:\\Program Files (x86)\\EPiServer\\CMS\\6.0.530.0\\Application\\</strong> on my machine.\r\n\r\nI found the following sites useful when looking into this:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971\">http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Templates/Forum/Pages/thread.aspx?id=40971\"></a><a href=\"http://www.markeverard.com/blog/2010/05/21/default-episerver-web-configs-for-iis6-and-iis7/\">http://www.markeverard.com/blog/2010/05/21/default-episerver-web-configs-for-iis6-and-iis7/</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6\"></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6\">http://epiwiki.se/configuration/webconfig-iis7-to-iis6</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/\"></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/\">http://world.episerver.com/en/Documentation/Items/Tech-Notes/EPiServer-CMS-5/EPiServer-CMS-5-R2-SP1/Changes-Between-IIS6-and-IIS7/</a>','EPiServer 6 in the Visual Studio development server','','inherit','open','open','','280-revision-9','','','2010-11-29 19:05:32','2010-11-29 19:05:32','',280,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/11/29/280-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(292,1,'2010-11-29 20:19:19','2010-11-29 20:19:19','','Jonathan Sewell','','inherit','open','open','','dscf3927_small','','','2010-11-29 20:19:19','2010-11-29 20:19:19','',2,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/DSCF3927_small.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(293,1,'2010-10-28 10:29:34','2010-10-28 09:29:34','This is my web development learning journal. It\'s a place for me to store useful code and information that I work with so I can refer back to it in the future. It\'s also a learning tool because writing down a problem or solution makes me think about it logically and helps me to understand it.\r\n\r\nI\'m a web developer and I work at <a title=\"The Cubeworks site\" href=\"http://www.cubeworks.co.uk\">Cubeworks </a>in <a title=\"Brighton on the map\" href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=brighton,+uk&amp;sll=53.800651,-4.064941&amp;sspn=20.824402,57.084961&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=Brighton,+East+Sussex,+United+Kingdom&amp;ll=50.819818,-0.131836&amp;spn=22.241089,57.084961&amp;z=5\">Brighton</a>.','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-3','','','2010-10-28 10:29:34','2010-10-28 09:29:34','',2,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/10/28/2-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(294,1,'2010-12-06 18:21:30','2010-12-06 18:21:30','EPiServer has a page about <a title=\"EPiServer exam knowledge areas\" href=\"http://www.episerver.com/en/Education/EPiServer-Certified--Developer/Knowledge-Areas/\">the areas you need to cover for the exam</a>.\r\n\r\nThere is <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/556221\">a Stackoverflow thread about the version 5 exam</a> that has some useful information.\r\n\r\n<strong>Some blog posts about the exam:</strong>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Rouslan Minasian\'s post\" href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Blogs/Rouslan-Minasian/Dates/2010/8/EPiServer-Certification/\">EPiServer Certification</a>, Rouslan Minasian\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Fredrick Haglund\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.fredrikhaglund.se/blog/2008/11/30/how-to-become-a-episerver-ceritified-developer/\">How to become a EPiServer Ceritified Developer</a>, Fredrik Haglund.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Mikael Lundin\'s post\" href=\"http://mint.litemedia.se/2008/11/29/episerver-cms-5-certified-developer/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified Developer</a>, Mikael Lundin\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Björn Sållarp\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.sallarp.com/episerver-cms-5-certified/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified!</a>, Björn Sållarp\r\n\r\nWhen I was preparing for the exam I re-read the administrator and editor manuals, the developer documentation in the SDK, and the tech notes. The tech notes form the bulk of the material and there are a lot of them so it\'s worth prioritising them somehow.','EPiServer 6 exam bookmarks','','publish','open','open','','episerver-6-exam-bookmarks','','http://blog.fredrikhaglund.se/blog/2008/11/30/how-to-become-a-episerver-ceritified-developer/\nhttp://mint.litemedia.se/2008/11/29/episerver-cms-5-certified-developer/\nhttp://blog.sallarp.com/episerver-cms-5-certified/','2010-12-06 18:21:54','2010-12-06 18:21:54','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=294',0,'post','',0),(295,1,'2010-12-06 18:07:20','2010-12-06 18:07:20','I\'ve got a few bookmarks to resources about the EPiServer 6 exam. I have sat and passed the EPiServer 6 exam, it\'s of a fairly high standard so you should put in some work to make sure you are prepared.\n\nEPiServer has a page about<a title=\"EPiServer exam knowledge areas\" href=\"http://www.episerver.com/en/Education/EPiServer-Certified--Developer/Knowledge-Areas/\"> the areas you need to cover for the exam</a>.\n\nThere is <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/556221\">a Stackoverflow thread about the version 5 exam</a> that has some useful information.\n\n<a title=\"Fredrick Haglund\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.fredrikhaglund.se/blog/2008/11/30/how-to-become-a-episerver-ceritified-developer/\">How to become a EPiServer Ceritified Developer</a>, by Fredrik Haglund.','EPiServer 6 exam resources','','inherit','open','open','','294-revision','','','2010-12-06 18:07:20','2010-12-06 18:07:20','',294,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/12/06/294-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(296,1,'2010-12-06 18:21:10','2010-12-06 18:21:10','I\'ve got a few bookmarks to resources about the EPiServer 6 exam:\n\nEPiServer has a page about <a title=\"EPiServer exam knowledge areas\" href=\"http://www.episerver.com/en/Education/EPiServer-Certified--Developer/Knowledge-Areas/\">the areas you need to cover for the exam</a>.\n\nThere is <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/556221\">a Stackoverflow thread about the version 5 exam</a> that has some useful information.\n\n<strong>Some blog posts about the exam:</strong>\n\n<a title=\"Rouslan Minasian\'s post\" href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Blogs/Rouslan-Minasian/Dates/2010/8/EPiServer-Certification/\">EPiServer Certification</a>, Rouslan Minasian\n\n<a title=\"Fredrick Haglund\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.fredrikhaglund.se/blog/2008/11/30/how-to-become-a-episerver-ceritified-developer/\">How to become a EPiServer Ceritified Developer</a>, Fredrik Haglund.\n\n<a title=\"Mikael Lundin\'s post\" href=\"http://mint.litemedia.se/2008/11/29/episerver-cms-5-certified-developer/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified Developer</a>, Mikael Lundin\n\n<a title=\"Björn Sållarp\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.sallarp.com/episerver-cms-5-certified/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified!</a>, Björn Sållarp\n\nWhen I was preparing for the exam I re-read the administrator and editor manuals, the developer documentation in the SDK, and the tech notes. The tech notes form the bulk of the material and there are a lot of them so choose the ones you think will get the most from and start there.','EPiServer 6 exam bookmarks','','inherit','open','open','','294-revision-2','','','2010-12-06 18:21:10','2010-12-06 18:21:10','',294,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/12/06/294-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(297,1,'2010-12-06 18:21:30','2010-12-06 18:21:30','I\'ve got a few bookmarks to resources about the EPiServer 6 exam:\r\n\r\nEPiServer has a page about <a title=\"EPiServer exam knowledge areas\" href=\"http://www.episerver.com/en/Education/EPiServer-Certified--Developer/Knowledge-Areas/\">the areas you need to cover for the exam</a>.\r\n\r\nThere is <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/556221\">a Stackoverflow thread about the version 5 exam</a> that has some useful information.\r\n\r\n<strong>Some blog posts about the exam:</strong>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Rouslan Minasian\'s post\" href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Blogs/Rouslan-Minasian/Dates/2010/8/EPiServer-Certification/\">EPiServer Certification</a>, Rouslan Minasian\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Fredrick Haglund\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.fredrikhaglund.se/blog/2008/11/30/how-to-become-a-episerver-ceritified-developer/\">How to become a EPiServer Ceritified Developer</a>, Fredrik Haglund.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Mikael Lundin\'s post\" href=\"http://mint.litemedia.se/2008/11/29/episerver-cms-5-certified-developer/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified Developer</a>, Mikael Lundin\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Björn Sållarp\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.sallarp.com/episerver-cms-5-certified/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified!</a>, Björn Sållarp\r\n\r\nWhen I was preparing for the exam I re-read the administrator and editor manuals, the developer documentation in the SDK, and the tech notes. The tech notes form the bulk of the material and there are a lot of them so it\'s worth prioritising them somehow.','EPiServer 6 exam bookmarks','','inherit','open','open','','294-revision-3','','','2010-12-06 18:21:30','2010-12-06 18:21:30','',294,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/12/06/294-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(299,1,'2010-12-08 18:07:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','I\'ve got a little net book with with Ubuntu net book edition.','A bit of Ruby','','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-12-08 18:07:24','2010-12-08 18:07:24','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=299',0,'post','',0),(300,1,'2010-12-08 17:40:38','2010-12-08 17:40:38','I\'ve got a little net book with with Ubuntu net book edition.','A bit of Ruby','','inherit','open','open','','299-revision','','','2010-12-08 17:40:38','2010-12-08 17:40:38','',299,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/12/08/299-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(301,1,'2010-12-09 16:37:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">public static string GetPageAsString(Uri address)\r\n{\r\nvar result = \"\";\r\nvar request = WebRequest.Create(address) as HttpWebRequest;\r\nusing (var response = request.GetResponse() as HttpWebResponse)\r\n{\r\nvar reader = new StreamReader(response.GetResponseStream());\r\nresult = reader.ReadToEnd();\r\n}\r\nreturn result;\r\n}\r\npublic static string GetPageAsString(Uri address)\r\n{\r\nvar result = \"\";\r\nvar request = WebRequest.Create(address) as HttpWebRequest;\r\nusing (var response = request.GetResponse() as HttpWebResponse)\r\n{\r\nvar reader = new StreamReader(response.GetResponseStream());	 result = reader.ReadToEnd();\r\n}\r\nreturn result;\r\n}</pre>','Snippet: System.Net.HTTPWebRequest','','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-12-09 16:37:01','2010-12-09 16:37:01','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=301',0,'post','',0),(302,1,'2010-12-09 16:35:33','2010-12-09 16:35:33','<pre class=\"brush:csharp\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">public static string GetPageAsString(Uri address)\n{\nvar result = \"\";\nvar request = WebRequest.Create(address) as HttpWebRequest;\nusing (var response = request.GetResponse() as HttpWebResponse)\n{\nvar reader = new StreamReader(response.GetResponseStream());\nresult = reader.ReadToEnd();\n}\nreturn result;\n}\npublic static string GetPageAsString(Uri address)\n{\nvar result = \"\";\nvar request = WebRequest.Create(address) as HttpWebRequest;\nusing (var response = request.GetResponse() as HttpWebResponse)\n{\nvar reader = new StreamReader(response.GetResponseStream());	 result = reader.ReadToEnd();\n}\nreturn result;\n}</pre>','Snippet: System.Net.HTTPWebRequest','','inherit','open','open','','301-revision','','','2010-12-09 16:35:33','2010-12-09 16:35:33','',301,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/12/09/301-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(303,1,'2010-12-09 16:36:33','2010-12-09 16:36:33','<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">public static string GetPageAsString(Uri address)\n{\nvar result = \"\";\nvar request = WebRequest.Create(address) as HttpWebRequest;\nusing (var response = request.GetResponse() as HttpWebResponse)\n{\nvar reader = new StreamReader(response.GetResponseStream());\nresult = reader.ReadToEnd();\n}\nreturn result;\n}\npublic static string GetPageAsString(Uri address)\n{\nvar result = \"\";\nvar request = WebRequest.Create(address) as HttpWebRequest;\nusing (var response = request.GetResponse() as HttpWebResponse)\n{\nvar reader = new StreamReader(response.GetResponseStream());	 result = reader.ReadToEnd();\n}\nreturn result;\n}</pre>','Snippet: System.Net.HTTPWebRequest','','inherit','open','open','','301-revision-2','','','2010-12-09 16:36:33','2010-12-09 16:36:33','',301,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/12/09/301-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(304,1,'2011-01-06 08:50:57','2011-01-06 08:50:57','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\r\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\r\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgit\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgit</a>. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".  More information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\r\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\r\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.  Take the public key from id_rsa.pub.  Test you can connect to github.com with the command:\r\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>\r\nThis is also a good time to set your username and email address in Git. Instructions are on GitHub <a href=\"http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/\">http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/</a>.\r\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\r\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.  Run install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".\r\n<h2>Configure your Merge Tool</h2>\r\nWe are using Beyond Compare 3. You can configure Git to use Beyond Compare by issuing configuration commands at the command prompt, but I prefer to paste them into the .gitconfig file (in C:\\users\\username\\ on my Windows 7 machine).\r\n<pre>[merge]\r\ntool = bc3\r\n[mergetool \"bc3\"]\r\ncmd = \\\"c:/program files/Beyond Compare 3/bcompare.exe\\\" \\\"$PWD/$LOCAL\\\" \\\"$PWD/$REMOTE\\\" \\\"$PWD/$BASE\\\" \\\"$PWD/$MERGED\\\"\r\nkeepBackup = false\r\ntrustExitCode = false</pre>','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','publish','open','open','','setting-up-git-in-windows-7','','','2011-01-22 21:40:21','2011-01-22 21:40:21','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=304',0,'post','',0),(305,1,'2011-01-06 08:40:27','2011-01-06 08:40:27','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required.\n\nI\'m following the GitHub help guide here: http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision','','','2011-01-06 08:40:27','2011-01-06 08:40:27','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(306,1,'2011-01-06 08:42:12','2011-01-06 08:42:12','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required.\n<h2><strong>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</strong></h2>\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".\n\nMore information GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys</h2>\n<h2>Useful Links</h2>','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-2','','','2011-01-06 08:42:12','2011-01-06 08:42:12','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(307,1,'2011-01-06 08:45:24','2011-01-06 08:45:24','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required.\n<h2><strong>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</strong></h2>\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".\n\nMore information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys</h2>\nStart the Git Bash console and foll','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-3','','','2011-01-06 08:45:24','2011-01-06 08:45:24','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(308,1,'2011-01-06 08:47:25','2011-01-06 08:47:25','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required.\n<h2><strong>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</strong></h2>\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".\n\nMore information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-4','','','2011-01-06 08:47:25','2011-01-06 08:47:25','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(309,1,'2011-01-06 08:50:16','2011-01-06 08:50:16','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required.\n<h2><strong>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</strong></h2>\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".\n\nMore information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.\n\nTake the public key from id_rsa.pub.\n\nTest you can connect to github.','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-5','','','2011-01-06 08:50:16','2011-01-06 08:50:16','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(310,1,'2011-01-22 21:41:28','2011-01-22 21:41:28','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgit\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgit</a>. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".  More information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.  Take the public key from id_rsa.pub.  Test you can connect to github.com with the command:\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>\nThis is also a good time to set your username and email address in Git. Instructions are on GitHub <a href=\"http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/\">http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/</a>.\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.  Run install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".\n<h2>Configure your Merge Tool</h2>\nWe are using Beyond Compare 3. You can configure Git to use Beyond Compare by issuing configuration commands at the command prompt, but I prefer to paste them into the .gitconfig file (in C:\\users\\username\\ on my Windows 7 machine).\n<pre>[merge]\ntool = bc3\n[mergetool \"bc3\"]\ncmd = \\\"c:/program files/Beyond Compare 3/bcompare.exe\\\" \\\"$PWD/$LOCAL\\\" \\\"$PWD/$REMOTE\\\" \\\"$PWD/$BASE\\\" \\\"$PWD/$MERGED\\\"\nkeepBackup = false\ntrustExitCode = false</pre>','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-autosave','','','2011-01-22 21:41:28','2011-01-22 21:41:28','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(311,1,'2011-01-06 08:50:57','2011-01-06 08:50:57','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\r\n<h2><strong>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</strong></h2>\r\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".\r\n\r\nMore information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\r\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\r\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.\r\n\r\nTake the public key from id_rsa.pub.\r\n\r\nTest you can connect to github.com with the command:\r\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-6','','','2011-01-06 08:50:57','2011-01-06 08:50:57','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2011-01-06 09:03:58','2011-01-06 09:03:58','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\r\n<h2><strong>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</strong></h2>\r\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".\r\n\r\nMore information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\r\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\r\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.\r\n\r\nTake the public key from id_rsa.pub.\r\n\r\nTest you can connect to github.com with the command:\r\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>\r\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\r\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.\r\n\r\nRun install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-7','','','2011-01-06 09:03:58','2011-01-06 09:03:58','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(313,1,'2011-01-06 09:05:48','2011-01-06 09:05:48','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\r\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\r\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgi\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgi</a>t. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".  More information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\r\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\r\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.  Take the public key from id_rsa.pub.  Test you can connect to github.com with the command:\r\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>\r\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\r\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.  Run install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-8','','','2011-01-06 09:05:48','2011-01-06 09:05:48','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(314,1,'2011-01-06 09:06:12','2011-01-06 09:06:12','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\r\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\r\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgit\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgit</a>. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".  More information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\r\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\r\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.  Take the public key from id_rsa.pub.  Test you can connect to github.com with the command:\r\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>\r\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\r\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.  Run install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-9','','','2011-01-06 09:06:12','2011-01-06 09:06:12','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(316,1,'2011-01-06 15:13:19','2011-01-06 15:13:19','This is a useful tip when you feel like pulling your hair out because you can\'t figure out why the EPiServer site you just published won\'t let you access the CMS. Trying to go to edit mode or admin mode just gives you an error:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-317\" title=\"EPiServer-custom-error\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/EPiServer-custom-error.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"573\" height=\"252\" />\r\n\r\nPage could not be loaded. The link you specified does not work. This may either be the result of temporary maintenance or an incorrect link. Well that\'s not helpful for a developer, so you just need to turn it off to see the ASP.NET error (yellow-screen-of-death).\r\n\r\nSimply set globalErrorHandling=\"Off\" in the &lt;siteSettings&gt; node.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-318\" title=\"Custom-errors-config\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Custom-errors-config.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"642\" height=\"209\" />','Tip: Turn Off EPiServer Custom Error Handling','','publish','open','open','','tip-turn-off-episerver-custom-error-handling','','','2011-01-06 16:23:15','2011-01-06 16:23:15','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=316',0,'post','',0),(317,1,'2011-01-06 15:08:02','2011-01-06 15:08:02','Page could not be loaded. The link you specified does not work. This may either be the result of temporary maintenance or an incorrect link. ','EPiServer-custom-error','','inherit','open','open','','episerver-custom-error','','','2011-01-06 15:08:02','2011-01-06 15:08:02','',316,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/EPiServer-custom-error.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(318,1,'2011-01-06 15:12:39','2011-01-06 15:12:39','','Custom-errors-config','','inherit','open','open','','custom-errors-config','','','2011-01-06 15:12:39','2011-01-06 15:12:39','',316,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Custom-errors-config.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(319,1,'2011-01-06 15:12:20','2011-01-06 15:12:20','This is a useful tip when you feel like pulling your hair out because you can\'t figure out why the EPiServer site you just published won\'t let you access the CMS. Trying to go to edit mode or admin mode just gives you an error:\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-317\" title=\"EPiServer-custom-error\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/EPiServer-custom-error.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"573\" height=\"252\" />\n\nPage could not be loaded. The link you specified does not work. This may either be the result of temporary maintenance or an incorrect link. Well that\'s not helpful for a developer, so you just need to turn it off to see the ASP.NET error (yellow-screen-of-death).\n\nSimply set globalErrorHandling=\"Off\" in the &lt;sites&gt;','Tip: Turn Off EPiServer Custom Error Handling','','inherit','open','open','','316-revision','','','2011-01-06 15:12:20','2011-01-06 15:12:20','',316,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/316-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2011-01-06 15:14:22','2011-01-06 15:14:22','This is a useful tip when you feel like pulling your hair out because you can\'t figure out why the EPiServer site you just published won\'t let you access the CMS. Trying to go to edit mode or admin mode just gives you an error:\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-317\" title=\"EPiServer-custom-error\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/EPiServer-custom-error.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"573\" height=\"252\" />\n\nPage could not be loaded. The link you specified does not work. This may either be the result of temporary maintenance or an incorrect link. Well that\'s not helpful for a developer, so you just need to turn it off to see the ASP.NET error (yellow-screen-of-death).\n\nSimply set globalErrorHandling=\"Off\" in the &lt;siteSettings&gt; node.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-318\" title=\"Custom-errors-config\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Custom-errors-config.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"642\" height=\"209\" />','Tip: Turn Off EPiServer Custom Error Handling','','inherit','open','open','','316-autosave','','','2011-01-06 15:14:22','2011-01-06 15:14:22','',316,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/316-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2011-01-06 15:13:19','2011-01-06 15:13:19','This is a useful tip when you feel like pulling your hair out because you can\'t figure out why the EPiServer site you just published won\'t let you access the CMS. Trying to go to edit mode or admin mode just gives you an error:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-317\" title=\"EPiServer-custom-error\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/EPiServer-custom-error.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"573\" height=\"252\" />\r\n\r\nPage could not be loaded. The link you specified does not work. This may either be the result of temporary maintenance or an incorrect link. Well that\'s not helpful for a developer, so you just need to turn it off to see the ASP.NET error (yellow-screen-of-death).\r\n\r\nSimply set globalErrorHandling=\"Off\" in the &lt;siteSettings&gt; node.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-318\" title=\"Custom-errors-config\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Custom-errors-config.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"642\" height=\"209\" />','Tip: Turn Off EPiServer Custom Error Handling','','inherit','open','open','','316-revision-2','','','2011-01-06 15:13:19','2011-01-06 15:13:19','',316,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/316-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(322,1,'2011-01-11 16:13:15','2011-01-11 16:13:15','Just had to fix a problem with an ASP.NET webforms site where hitting enter in a form took the user to the search results page. The site search button at the top of the page was being selected as the default button.\r\n\r\nThe solution is to set the \"DefaultButton\" property of the form:\r\n<pre>Page.Form.DefaultButton = buttonUpdate.UniqueID;</pre>\r\nMore information:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://geekswithblogs.net/ranganh/archive/2006/04/12/74951.aspx\">http://geekswithblogs.net/ranganh/archive/2006/04/12/74951.aspx</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://imar.spaanjaars.com/374/how-do-i-set-the-defaultfocus-or-defaultbutton-in-a-page-based-on-a-master-page-in-aspnet-20\">http://imar.spaanjaars.com/374/how-do-i-set-the-defaultfocus-or-defaultbutton-in-a-page-based-on-a-master-page-in-aspnet-20</a>','Default form button problem','','publish','open','open','','default-form-button-problem','','\nhttp://geekswithblogs.net/ranganh/archive/2006/04/12/74951.aspx','2011-01-11 16:16:28','2011-01-11 16:16:28','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=322',0,'post','',0),(323,1,'2011-01-11 16:13:11','2011-01-11 16:13:11','Just had to fix a problem with an ASP.NET webforms site where hitting enter in a form took the user to the search results page. The site search button at the top of the page was being selected as the default button.\n\nThe solution is to set the \"DefaultButton\" property of the form:\n<pre>Page.Form.DefaultButton = buttonUpdate.UniqueID;</pre>\nMore information:\n\n<a href=\"http://geekswithblogs.net/ranganh/archive/2006/04/12/74951.aspx\">http://geekswithblogs.net/ranganh/archive/2006/04/12/74951.aspx</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://imar.spaanjaars.com/374/how-do-i-set-the-defaultfocus-or-defaultbutton-in-a-page-based-on-a-master-page-in-aspnet-20\">http://imar.spaanjaars.com/374/how-do-i-set-the-defaultfocus-or-defaultbutton-in-a-page-based-on-a-master-page-in-aspnet-20</a>','Default form button problem','','inherit','open','open','','322-revision','','','2011-01-11 16:13:11','2011-01-11 16:13:11','',322,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/11/322-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(324,1,'2011-01-11 16:13:15','2011-01-11 16:13:15','Just had to fix a problem with an ASP.NET webforms site where hitting enter in a form took the user to the search results page. The site search button at the top of the page was being selected as the default button.\r\n\r\nThe solution is to set the \"DefaultButton\" property of the form:\r\n<pre>Page.Form.DefaultButton = buttonUpdate.UniqueID;</pre>\r\nMore information:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://geekswithblogs.net/ranganh/archive/2006/04/12/74951.aspx\">http://geekswithblogs.net/ranganh/archive/2006/04/12/74951.aspx</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://imar.spaanjaars.com/374/how-do-i-set-the-defaultfocus-or-defaultbutton-in-a-page-based-on-a-master-page-in-aspnet-20\">http://imar.spaanjaars.com/374/how-do-i-set-the-defaultfocus-or-defaultbutton-in-a-page-based-on-a-master-page-in-aspnet-20</a>','Default form button problem','','inherit','open','open','','322-revision-2','','','2011-01-11 16:13:15','2011-01-11 16:13:15','',322,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/11/322-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(325,1,'2011-01-13 22:17:13','2011-01-13 22:17:13','One of the problems with the default install of EPiServer 6 is that you can\'t use a relative path for virtual path providers (which map virtual URLs to files in the file manager). This means that while I have these files at <strong>D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP</strong> and another developer pulls my code out of source control they will have a problem because they put the project in <strong>F:\\development\\LatestEPiServerProject</strong>.\r\n\r\nWe can avoid these problems by using a relative path in the .config file. So:\r\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\r\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\r\ntype=\"EPiServer.Web.Hosting.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,EPiServer\"\r\n<strong><em>physicalPath=\"D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents</em>\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\r\nbecomes:\r\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\r\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\r\n<strong><em>type=\"MyEPiServerExtensions.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,MyEPiServerExtensions\"\r\nphysicalPath=\"~\\..\\VPP\\Documents\"</em></strong> /&gt;</pre>\r\nI need to go up a directory and back down to the VPP folder, I have folder structure:\r\n\r\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\r\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\Site\\\r\n\r\nThe new provider type is simply a thin wrapper that converts relative paths to physical paths that the EPiServer implementation can continue to work with.\r\n\r\nThe code is on Github at <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/778715\">https://gist.github.com/778715</a>','Use a relative path with Virtual Path Providers','','publish','open','open','','use-a-relative-path-with-virtual-path-providers','','','2011-01-13 22:26:37','2011-01-13 22:26:37','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=325',0,'post','',0),(326,1,'2011-01-13 22:16:54','2011-01-13 22:16:54','One of the problems with the default install of EPiServer 6 is that you can\'t use a relative path for virtual path providers (which map virtual URLs to files in the file manager). This means that while I have these files at <strong>D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP</strong> and another developer pulls my code out of source control they will have a problem because they put the project in <strong>F:\\development\\LatestEPiServerProject</strong>.\n\nWe can avoid these problems by using a relative path in the .config file. So:\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\ntype=\"EPiServer.Web.Hosting.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,EPiServer\"\n<strong>physicalPath=\"D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\nbecomes:\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\n<strong>type=\"MyEPiServerExtensions.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,MyEPiServerExtensions\"</strong>\n<strong>physicalPath=\"~\\..\\VPP\\Documents\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\nI need to go up a directory and back down to the VPP folder, I have folder structure:\n\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\Site\\\n\nThe new provider type is simply a thin wrapper that converts relative paths to physical paths that the EPiServer implementation can continue to work with.\n\nThe code is on Github at <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/778715\">https://gist.github.com/778715</a>','Use a relative path with Virtual Path Providers','','inherit','open','open','','325-revision','','','2011-01-13 22:16:54','2011-01-13 22:16:54','',325,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/13/325-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(327,1,'2011-01-13 22:18:23','2011-01-13 22:18:23','One of the problems with the default install of EPiServer 6 is that you can\'t use a relative path for virtual path providers (which map virtual URLs to files in the file manager). This means that while I have these files at <strong>D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP</strong> and another developer pulls my code out of source control they will have a problem because they put the project in <strong>F:\\development\\LatestEPiServerProject</strong>.\n\nWe can avoid these problems by using a relative path in the .config file. So:\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\ntype=\"EPiServer.Web.Hosting.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,EPiServer\"\n<strong>physicalPath=\"D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\nbecomes:\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\n<strong>type=\"MyEPiServerExtensions.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,MyEPiServerExtensions\"</strong>\n<strong>physicalPath=\"~\\..\\VPP\\Documents\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\nI need to go up a directory and back down to the VPP folder, I have folder structure:\n\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\Site\\\n\nThe new provider type is simply a thin wrapper that converts relative paths to physical paths that the EPiServer implementation can continue to work with.\n\nThe code is on Github at <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/778715\">https://gist.github.com/778715</a>','Use a relative path with Virtual Path Providers','','inherit','open','open','','325-autosave','','','2011-01-13 22:18:23','2011-01-13 22:18:23','',325,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/13/325-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(328,1,'2011-01-13 22:17:13','2011-01-13 22:17:13','One of the problems with the default install of EPiServer 6 is that you can\'t use a relative path for virtual path providers (which map virtual URLs to files in the file manager). This means that while I have these files at <strong>D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP</strong> and another developer pulls my code out of source control they will have a problem because they put the project in <strong>F:\\development\\LatestEPiServerProject</strong>.\r\n\r\nWe can avoid these problems by using a relative path in the .config file. So:\r\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\r\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\r\ntype=\"EPiServer.Web.Hosting.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,EPiServer\"\r\n<strong>physicalPath=\"D:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\r\nbecomes:\r\n<pre>&lt;add showInFileManager=\"true\" virtualName=\"Documents\" virtualPath=\"~/Documents/\"\r\nbypassAccessCheck=\"false\" maxVersions=\"5\" name=\"SiteDocuments\"\r\n<strong>type=\"MyEPiServerExtensions.VirtualPathVersioningProvider,MyEPiServerExtensions\"</strong>\r\n<strong>physicalPath=\"~\\..\\VPP\\Documents\"</strong> /&gt;</pre>\r\nI need to go up a directory and back down to the VPP folder, I have folder structure:\r\n\r\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\VPP\\Documents\r\nD:\\LatestEPiServerProject\\Site\\\r\n\r\nThe new provider type is simply a thin wrapper that converts relative paths to physical paths that the EPiServer implementation can continue to work with.\r\n\r\nThe code is on Github at <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/778715\">https://gist.github.com/778715</a>','Use a relative path with Virtual Path Providers','','inherit','open','open','','325-revision-2','','','2011-01-13 22:17:13','2011-01-13 22:17:13','',325,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/13/325-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(329,1,'2011-01-22 21:31:57','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2011-01-22 21:31:57','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=329',0,'post','',0),(330,1,'2011-01-06 11:24:14','2011-01-06 11:24:14','I\'ve got a new install of Windows 7 and need to install Git. These are the steps required:\r\n<h2>Install Git for Windows (mysysgit)</h2>\r\nDownload and run the setup file from <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/msysgit\">http://code.google.com/p/msysgit</a>. Make sure to select \"<strong>Run Git from the Windows Command Prompt</strong>\" and then \"<strong>Checkout as-is, commit as-is</strong>\".  More information is in GitHub help guide http://help.github.com/win-git-installation/.\r\n<h2>Generate SSH Keys for GitHub</h2>\r\nStart the Git Bash console and follow the instructions on GitHib help <a href=\"http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/\">http://help.github.com/msysgit-key-setup/</a>.  Take the public key from id_rsa.pub.  Test you can connect to github.com with the command:\r\n<pre>ssh git@github.com</pre>\r\nThis is also a good time to set your username and email address in Git. Instructions are on GitHub <a href=\"http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/\">http://help.github.com/git-email-settings/</a>.\r\n<h2>Install PoshGit</h2>\r\nClone the PoshGit project, it\'s on GithHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git\">https://github.com/dahlbyk/posh-git</a>.  Run install.ps1. If you get an error like \"the execution of scripts is disabled on this system\", make sure you Powershell execution policy is set to \"RemoteUnsigned\" using command \"Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteUnsigned\".','Setting up Git in Windows 7','','inherit','open','open','','304-revision-10','','','2011-01-06 11:24:14','2011-01-06 11:24:14','',304,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/06/304-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(331,1,'2011-01-23 18:14:39','2011-01-23 18:14:39','EPiServer has a page about <a title=\"EPiServer exam knowledge areas\" href=\"http://www.episerver.com/en/Education/EPiServer-Certified--Developer/Knowledge-Areas/\">the areas you need to cover for the exam</a>.\n\nThere is <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/556221\">a Stackoverflow thread about the version 5 exam</a> that has some useful information.\n\n<strong>Some blog posts about the exam:</strong>\n\nEPiServer 6 Exam Sections\n\n<a title=\"Rouslan Minasian\'s post\" href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Blogs/Rouslan-Minasian/Dates/2010/8/EPiServer-Certification/\">EPiServer Certification</a>, Rouslan Minasian\n\n<a title=\"Fredrick Haglund\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.fredrikhaglund.se/blog/2008/11/30/how-to-become-a-episerver-ceritified-developer/\">How to become a EPiServer Ceritified Developer</a>, Fredrik Haglund.\n\n<a title=\"Mikael Lundin\'s post\" href=\"http://mint.litemedia.se/2008/11/29/episerver-cms-5-certified-developer/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified Developer</a>, Mikael Lundin\n\n<a title=\"Björn Sållarp\'s post\" href=\"http://blog.sallarp.com/episerver-cms-5-certified/\">EPiServer CMS 5 Certified!</a>, Björn Sållarp\n\nWhen I was preparing for the exam I re-read the administrator and editor manuals, the developer documentation in the SDK, and the tech notes. The tech notes form the bulk of the material and there are a lot of them so it\'s worth prioritising them somehow.','EPiServer 6 exam bookmarks','','inherit','open','open','','294-autosave','','','2011-01-23 18:14:39','2011-01-23 18:14:39','',294,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2011/01/23/294-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(332,1,'2010-09-07 16:59:39','2010-09-07 15:59:39','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre or any of the installers on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed. So how do you get the EPiServer Scheduler Service installed on the web server?  Any Admin Mode page that relies on the scheduler service is showing a warning: \"The EPiServer Scheduler Service does not  appear to be active, it may have been stopped.\"\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" title=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" src=\"http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/EPiServer-scheduler-service.jpg\" alt=\"EPiServer-scheduler-service\" width=\"770\" height=\"134\" />\r\n\r\nIn order to maintain maximum control over what is installed on the web server you might try to install the service using the <strong>installutil </strong>program. I tried this approach, I copied the EPiServer scheduler service files from \"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\EPiServer\\Shared\\Services\\Scheduler Service\" and ran the command:\r\n\r\n<strong>installutil EPiServer.SchedulerSvc.exe</strong>\r\n\r\nBut this doesn\'t work and you\'ll get an error:\r\n\r\n<strong>No public installers with the RunInstallerAttribute.Yes attribute could be found in the D:\\sites\\jisc-collections.ac.uk\\EPiServerSchedulerService5.2.375.236\\EPiServer.SchedulerSvc.exe assembly.</strong>\r\n\r\nThe scheduler service is not designed to be manually installed like this. As such your only option is to install it using <strong>EPiServerShared.msi</strong> from the EPiServer CMS installation files (available on <a href=\"http://world.episerver.com/Download/Categories/Products/EPiServer-CMS/\">EPiServer World</a>). This will install and start 3 services and won\'t require you to restart the machine:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>EPiServer Scheduler Service</li>\r\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Log Service</li>\r\n	<li>EPiServer CMS Indexing Service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIt\'s not an ideal solution if you like to maintain absolute control over what is installed on the web server, but it\'s a quick and easy install that does work.','Installing the EPiServer Scheduler Service','We have our own (XCopy type) deployment process and don\'t use the EPiServer Deployment Centre or any of the installers on our web servers, as a result the scheduler service is not installed. So how do you get the EPiServer Scheduler Service installed on the web server?','inherit','open','open','','204-revision-6','','','2010-09-07 16:59:39','2010-09-07 15:59:39','',204,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/index.php/2010/09/07/204-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0);
